redcap:Surveys.title: Mesulam Center Recruitment Registry
redcap:Surveys.instructions:
MESULAM CENTER RESEARCH STUDY COVID-19 UPDATE

Please note that not all studies are actively recruiting due to the COVID-19 pandemic. We are working hard to continue our research, and as such, response times may vary. We appreciate your interest in our aging and dementia research.

 

Introduction
In order to participate in research at the Mesulam Center, we ask that you join our registry. Your participation in the registry helps us determine your eligibility for currently enrolling studies. Please read the following information carefully. Make sure that you understand it to your complete satisfaction before agreeing to participate.

Why are you being asked to join this registry?
We are asking you to join our registry because you are interested in participating in research at our Center. Because many of our studies have strict eligibility criteria and involve specific research activities, your participation in this registry will help us determine your eligibility for our research. Joining the registry does not guarantee your participation in research at our Center.

What should I know about this registry?
Participating in this registry is completely voluntary. If you choose not to participate, we will be unable to determine your eligibility for our research. You can agree to participate and change your mind later.

Who can I talk to?
If you have questions, concerns, or complaints, please contact our center at (312) 908-9339 or adc@northwestern.edu.

This research has been reviewed and approved by an Institutional Review Board ("IRB"). You may talk to them at (312) 503-9338 or irb@northwestern.edu if:
Your questions, concerns, or complaints are not being answered by the research team.
You cannot reach the research team.
You want to talk to someone besides the research team.
You have questions about your rights as a research participant.
You want to get information or provide input about this research.

What happens if I say, "Yes, I want to be in this registry"?
If you agree to participate, you will be asked to complete an online survey. In the survey, you will be asked questions about contact information, basic demographic information, medical history, and specific interests related to research activities. The survey will take approximately 10 minutes to complete. After you complete the survey, our staff will review your responses to see if you are eligible for any currently enrolling study or studies. If we determine that you are eligible, a staff member will contact you to discuss the study for which you are eligible. You can choose not to participate in a study for which you are eligible. If you complete the survey and are not contacted by a staff member, it is because we currently do not have any enrolling studies for which you are eligible. We will keep your information on file and will contact you in the future for any studies for which you are eligible.

What happens if I do not want to be in this registry?
You can decide not to participate in this registry and it will not be held against you. If you do not participate in this registry, we will be unable to determine your eligibility for our research.

What happens if I say "Yes", but I change my mind later?
You can leave the registry at any time and it will not be held against you. To do so, please contact our Center at (312) 908-9339 or adc@northwestern.edu.

Is there any way being in this registry could be bad for me?
There is a risk of breach of confidentiality, but measures are in place to help protect against this risk. Efforts will be made to limit the use and disclosure of your personal information to people who have a need to review this information. We cannot promise complete secrecy. Organizations that may inspect and copy your information include the IRB and other representatives of this institution.

What happens to the information collected for the registry?
The survey is being hosted by Northwestern University and involves a secure connection. All information will be kept on a password-protected computer only accessible by the approved staff members.

What else do I need to know?
You can begin the online survey and return to it at a later time. You will need to obtain a return code to reenter the online survey. In order to retrieve your return code, please call
(312) 908-9339 or email adc@northwestern.edu.
redcap:Surveys.acknowledgement:
MESULAM CENTER RESEARCH STUDY COVID-19 UPDATE

Please note that not all studies are actively recruiting due to the COVID-19 pandemic. We are working hard to continue our research, and as such, response times may vary. We appreciate your interest in our aging and dementia research.

 

What's next?

Your information will be reviewed by Mesulam Center research staff to see if you are potentially eligible for one or more of our research studies. If you are potentially eligible for currently enrolling studies, you will be contacted by our research staff. Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, you may not hear from a research staff person for weeks to months. There is also the possibility that upon review of your survey research staff determine that you are not currently eligible for any of our research studies. Sit tight, though! We are conducting new studies every year and by consenting to the Mesulam Center Recruitment Registry, we will keep your information and contact you in the future if we find you eligible for a new study.

 

Worried about your memory?

If you have immediate concerns about your memory or other changes in thinking, speaking, and judgment, we encourage you to contact your primary care provider. You may also seek a consultation at the Neurobehavior and Memory Clinic at Northwestern Medicine. Visit their website here or call them at (312) 695-9627.

 

Want to learn more about the Mesulam Center?

Check us out on our website and Facebook.

 

For questions or concerns, please contact (312) 908-9339 or adc@northwestern.edu.

redcap:Surveys.confirmation_email_content:
This email is confirming that we have received your submission for potential research participation at the Mesulam Center for Cognitive Neurology and Alzheimer's Disease of Northwestern University. We thank you for your interest. Research participants allow us to learn more about healthy aging and dementia. We are extremely grateful for all our research participants.

Please note that not all studies are actively recruiting due to the COVID-19 pandemic. We are working hard to continue our research, and as such, response times may vary. As a reminder, your information will be reviewed by Mesulam Center research staff to see if you are potentially eligible for one or more of our research studies. If you are potentially eligible for currently enrolling studies, you will be contacted by our research staff. Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, you may not hear from a research staff person for weeks to months. There is also the possibility that upon review of your survey research staff determine that you are not currently eligible for any of our research studies.

Sit tight, though! We are conducting new studies every year and by consenting to the Mesulam Center Recruitment Registry, we will keep your information and contact you in the future if we find you eligible for a new study.

If you have immediate concerns about your memory or other changes in thinking, speaking, and judgment, we encourage you to contact your primary care provider. You may also seek a consultation at the Neurobehavior and Memory Clinic at Northwestern Medicine. Visit their website here or call them at (312) 695-9627.

If you'd like to learn more about the Mesulam Center, check us out on our website and Facebook.

For questions or concerns, please contact (312) 908-9339 or adc@northwestern.edu.

redcap:Alerts.alert_message:
Hello Mesulam Center Recruitment Team!

New participants have been added to Ripple from the REDCap registry survey. To review newly added participants, click the link below. 

REDCap Report with newly added Ripple participants:

Below is information about what is included in the report:

  1. The "Participant already exists in Ripple?" column identifies whether the participant is a "New" participant added to Ripple or an "Existing" participant, meaning that they already exist in Ripple and their information has been updated accordingly.
  2. The "Date added to Ripple" indicates the date that each participant was added from REDCap to Ripple. All participants that have been added to Ripple are on this report, but the most recent batch of participants will be at the top of the report. 
  3. The report also contains the participant's name, contact information, diagnosis, and recruitment source information. 
  4. The Ripple Global ID and REDCap ID are also included so that participants can be looked up by their IDs rather than just their names in each database.

Thanks, 

Debby

The purpose of this form is to automatically send the registry survey link to care partners or patients in clinic that are interested in Mesulam Center ORE Core activities. This form only works if the person is interested in ORE Core activities and fills out the registry survey for themself (not on behalf of another person). If the person is not interested in ORE Core activities but is interested in other Mesulam Center activities, please direct them to the Mesulam Center website to join the Registry through there. In order for this form to trigger an email to be sent to the care partner or patient, question 5 must be answered as "Yes" and the person's email address must be provided in question 9. Once all fields are filled out and this form is marked as "Complete", an email with the registry survey link to be sent to the person.

If the person is not interested in ORE Core activities but is interested in other Mesulam Center activities, please direct them to the Mesulam Center website to join the Registry through there. In order for this form to trigger an email to be sent to the care partner or patient, question 5 must be answered as "Yes" and the person's email address must be provided in question 9.
